[[The Scar]] is an area of the [[Abyssal Space]], accessed by talking to the [[Catalytic Guardian]] in the [[Temple of the Eye (location)|Temple of the Eye]]. To reach the Leviathan in the Scar, players must proceed east of the [[Abyssal Rift (The Scar)|Abyssal Rift]] towards [[Wizard Persten]]'s camp. A rowboat there can then be used to reach the island where the Leviathan is located. Climbing the [[Handholds (The Leviathan)|handholds]] onto the platform initiates the fight momentarily.

A [[Scoreboard (The Leviathan)|scoreboard]] just before the rowboat shows statistics related to the Leviathan.

==Fight overview==
{{Main|The Leviathan/Strategies}}
The Leviathan is best fought with [[ranged]]; attempting to attack The Leviathan with [[melee]] will result in the following message: {{mes|Your melee attacks can't reach the lure!}} The boss fight is initiated upon climbing into the arena, where it will use a volley of rapid-firing attacks which deal damage upon impact; protection prayers will fully block these attacks.
[[File:Fighting the Leviathan.png|thumb|left|250px|A player fighting the Leviathan.]]
The Leviathan will attack with random volleys of coloured orbs - magic (blue), ranged (green), and melee (orange) - at varying attack speeds throughout the fight. At the end of each volley, the boss will roar and cause debris to fall onto the player, potentially restricting movement and obstructing line of sight. Every subsequent volley of attacks will increase in attack speed, which can become very difficult to switch prayers for players at later volleys. The boss can also bite players in the tiles right next to the pool, which deals melee damage.

At any point during the sequence, players can cast [[shadow spells]] to stun the Leviathan (which will always succeed), where it will stay still for 15 [[ticks]] (9 seconds). Damage against it is capped at 10 when stunned, but the player can run around to attack the gaping wound on its backside to deal a large amount of damage, which will cause it to retaliate with a special attack. This also resets the Leviathan's attack speed to the beginning of the 2-tick attacks.

Upon reaching 180 hitpoints, the Leviathan will begin the enrage phase. Its attack speed will now stay at two ticks, losing the ability to launch orange melee orbs (but still being able to bite players) while an [[abyssal pathfinder]] will spawn to the north-west of the arena (or the next clockwise direction if the spawn point is blocked by debris) and will begin to move clockwise. The player must stay within the pathfinder's area-of-effect in order to gain increased accuracy and damage, along with full protection from its attacks; otherwise, its attacks will pierce through prayer.

==Awakened version==
The Leviathan can also be '''awakened''' by use of an [[Awakener's orb]], greatly increasing the boss' stats and increasing the difficulty of the mechanics for a much harder fight.
For an overview of the differences between the regular and awakened versions of the boss, see this [[The Leviathan/Strategies#Awakened mode|strategy guide]].

